 total assets  billion website wwwlonestarfundscom lone star funds is an american private equity firm that invests in distressed assets in the us canada and internationally the founder of lone star established its first fund in  under a different name and lone star has to date organized fifteen private equity funds with total capital commitments since inception of over  billion as of june  lone star’s investors include corporate and public pension funds sovereign wealth funds university endowments foundations fund of funds and highnetworth individuals lone star funds has affiliate offices in north america europe and japan hudson advisors llc an approximately person global asset management company owned and controlled by the founder of lone star performs due diligence and analysis asset management and related services for lone star funds in this capacity hudson advisors llc has managed in excess of  billion of assets for lone star funds since inception contents  history  investment approach  motion picture financing  funds investment vehicles  references  external links historyedit lone star was founded by john grayken from  to  mr grayken was chairman and ceo of brazos partners lp a joint venture between the robert m bass group and the federal deposit insurance corporation that resolved approximately  “bad bank” assets resulting from the us savings and loan crisis in the early ‘s during this period brazos advisors llc was formed to provide assetmanagement and related services to brazos partners following brazos partners grayken organized institutional capital to continue investing in distressed assets closing brazos fund lp in  with approximately  million of capital commitments lone star opportunity fund lp followed in  with approximately  million of capital commitments at that time brazos advisors llc was renamed hudson advisors llc after an expansion into canada in  and  grayken pursued the launch of a global platform for lone star in  since then lone star has invested extensively in north america europe and east asia lone star invested primarily in east asia including japan korea indonesia and taiwan following the asian financial crisis in the late s in the mids following the establishment of the eurozone lone star increased its investment focus in europe and with the onset of the global financial crisis from  lone star was again actively investing in the us in july  lone star acquired the uk property investment and development company quintain for £ million in march  the portuguese central bank announced that lone star funds will acquire  of third largest portuguese bank novo banco in return for a capital injection of €bn the other  will be retained by the portuguese banks resolution fund investment approachedit lone star invests in a variety of asset classes primarily distressed opportunities in developed markets motion picture financingedit through its credit affiliate lstar capital officially lsc film corporation the company entered the motion picture financing sector when they signed a  million deal with sony pictures in early  the deal gives them a financial stake in nearly all of sonys upcoming films however due the poor boxoffice performance of sonys movies the two firms severed ties ended on july   two years before the deal was set to end funds investment vehiclesedit fund vintage year committed capital lone star real estate fund iv  b lone star residential mortgage fund i  b lone star fund ix  b lone star real estate fund iii  b lone star fund viii  b lone star fund vii  b lone star real estate fund ii  b lone star fund vi  b lone star real estate fund  b lone star fund v  b lone star fund iv  b lone star fund iii  b lone star fund ii  b lone star opportunity fund  m brazos fund  m  referencesedit  fund summary   ellie pullen april   lone star and credit suisse buy €bn rpi portfolio unquotecom   kardan sells  stake in cee real estate company gtc sa property eu november     chad eric watt august   lone star selling